# Snyk (https://snyk.io) policy file.
# Controls how `snyk test` / `snyk monitor` treat findings.
version: v1.25.0

# NOTE: there are no dependency (Open Source) ignores. The former ip@2.0.1 SSRF
# CVEs were FIXED at the root by overriding the transitive `ip` dependency to the
# maintained, CVE-free fork `neoip` (see `overrides` in the root package.json) —
# `ip@2.0.1` no longer resolves in the tree, so there is nothing to ignore.

# --- Snyk Code (SAST) path excludes ------------------------------------------
# `snyk ignore` cannot mark Code findings (the CLI: "Ignoring ... using the
# .snyk file is not supported for Snyk Code") — but Snyk Code honors
# `exclude.code` path globs. Every finding in these paths is a false positive
# and none ship in the product:
#   - **/*.test.ts(x)    : fake credentials in test fixtures
#   - apps/ui/vite/**     : dev-only Vite proxy (build tooling, not shipped)
#   - packages/i18n-dev/**: local i18n dev tooling (not a production endpoint)
exclude:
  code:
    - "**/*.test.ts"
    - "**/*.test.tsx"
    - "apps/ui/vite/**"
    - "packages/i18n-dev/**"
